00:00:19.505 --> 00:00:21.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: You might know
my next guest, Dr. John Gray,

00:00:21.880 --> 00:00:24.760 align:middle line:84%
as a relationship expert and
author of the bestselling book,

00:00:24.760 --> 00:00:26.630 align:middle line:84%
"Men Are from Mars,
Women Are from Venus."

00:00:26.630 --> 00:00:28.510 align:middle line:84%
But what you may
not know is John

00:00:28.510 --> 00:00:32.560 align:middle line:84%
is a 50-year meditator, who
studied sacred techniques

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:33.760 align:middle line:90%
with the Maharishi.

00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:35.890 align:middle line:10%
He was a celibate monk
who lived with Maharishi

00:00:35.890 --> 00:00:38.470 align:middle line:10%
as his personal
assistant for nine years.

00:00:38.470 --> 00:00:40.180 align:middle line:10%
And he's here today
to share with us

00:00:40.180 --> 00:00:42.530 align:middle line:10%
the natural
resonance meditation.

00:00:42.530 --> 00:00:43.330 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:00:43.330 --> 00:00:44.600 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for being here.

00:00:44.600 --> 00:00:45.300 align:middle line:90%
>>JOHN GRAY: Thank you, Lisa.

00:00:45.300 --> 00:00:45.840 align:middle line:90%
My pleasure.

00:00:45.840 --> 00:00:46.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This is exciting.

00:00:46.270 --> 00:00:47.200 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yeah.

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:48.820 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So this is
something that you

00:00:48.820 --> 00:00:50.590 align:middle line:10%
created over your years.

00:00:50.590 --> 00:00:53.710 align:middle line:10%
>>GRAY: Well, Maharishi taught
me transcendental meditation.

00:00:53.710 --> 00:00:54.650 align:middle line:10%
That was really big.

00:00:54.650 --> 00:00:56.530 align:middle line:10%
It still is, around the country.

00:00:56.530 --> 00:00:58.640 align:middle line:90%
The Beatles had gone to India.

00:00:58.640 --> 00:01:01.810 align:middle line:84%
And I had been in my room
listening to the Moody Blues.

00:01:01.810 --> 00:01:05.950 align:middle line:84%
And my mother walked in, and
she was in awe of this music

00:01:05.950 --> 00:01:07.640 align:middle line:90%
because they had this "Om."

00:01:07.640 --> 00:01:08.890 align:middle line:90%
And my mother was a meditator.

00:01:08.890 --> 00:01:09.830 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know.

00:01:09.830 --> 00:01:10.630 align:middle line:90%
And so she saw me.

00:01:10.630 --> 00:01:12.422 align:middle line:84%
I'm just sitting there,
listening to music.

00:01:12.422 --> 00:01:13.930 align:middle line:84%
She sat down,
meditated next to me.

00:01:13.930 --> 00:01:15.460 align:middle line:90%
And I got really high.

00:01:15.460 --> 00:01:17.790 align:middle line:84%
And then she saw the
poster on my wall.

00:01:17.790 --> 00:01:20.620 align:middle line:84%
I had a lot of Jimi Hendrix
posters and the whole thing.

00:01:20.620 --> 00:01:23.350 align:middle line:84%
And then there was
one of the Beatles,

00:01:23.350 --> 00:01:25.630 align:middle line:84%
with Maharishi
sitting in the center.

00:01:25.630 --> 00:01:26.860 align:middle line:90%
So she said, who's that?

00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:28.060 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't know.

00:01:28.060 --> 00:01:31.390 align:middle line:84%
But she had such
excitement about it.

00:01:31.390 --> 00:01:33.400 align:middle line:84%
I was curiosity
about meditation.

00:01:33.400 --> 00:01:35.943 align:middle line:84%
And then a few days
later-- synchronicity--

00:01:35.943 --> 00:01:38.110 align:middle line:84%
I was at the bowling alley,
and somebody said to me,

00:01:38.110 --> 00:01:40.660 align:middle line:84%
oh, there's a samurai
warrior demonstration.

00:01:40.660 --> 00:01:42.160 align:middle line:90%
You should go upstairs.

00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:45.220 align:middle line:84%
And I went, wow, because I was
in martial arts at the time.

00:01:45.220 --> 00:01:48.040 align:middle line:84%
And so I went up looking for
a martial arts demonstration,

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:50.680 align:middle line:84%
and it was a transcendental
meditation seminar.

00:01:50.680 --> 00:01:52.030 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:01:52.030 --> 00:01:53.890 align:middle line:90%
So my friend got the word right.

00:01:53.890 --> 00:01:57.100 align:middle line:84%
But when I heard the talk,
the basic, introductory talk

00:01:57.100 --> 00:02:00.680 align:middle line:84%
to transcendental meditation, it
just rang a bell inside of me.

00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:02.890 align:middle line:84%
It's like I was born
to hear that talk.

00:02:02.890 --> 00:02:04.600 align:middle line:84%
And when I came
home two hours late,

00:02:04.600 --> 00:02:06.070 align:middle line:84%
my dad said, so
why are you late?

00:02:06.070 --> 00:02:08.195 align:middle line:84%
And he thought I was off
with friends or something.

00:02:08.195 --> 00:02:09.707 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I went to the talk.

00:02:09.707 --> 00:02:11.290 align:middle line:84%
And he says, well,
what did you learn?

00:02:11.290 --> 00:02:12.682 align:middle line:90%
And I gave the whole talk.

00:02:12.682 --> 00:02:14.140 align:middle line:84%
I could still give
that whole talk.

00:02:14.140 --> 00:02:15.710 align:middle line:90%
It's right written in my heart.

00:02:15.710 --> 00:02:17.347 align:middle line:90%
It was a destiny for me.

00:02:17.347 --> 00:02:19.930 align:middle line:84%
It was one of those things where
all the bells in Heaven rang.

00:02:19.930 --> 00:02:21.200 align:middle line:90%
And I loved it.

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:22.210 align:middle line:90%
I learned to meditate.

00:02:22.210 --> 00:02:24.040 align:middle line:90%
I did transcendental meditation.

00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:26.800 align:middle line:84%
It's where you close your
eyes, and you repeat a mantra.

00:02:26.800 --> 00:02:29.050 align:middle line:84%
And you just repeat the
mantra over and over and over.

00:02:29.050 --> 00:02:31.420 align:middle line:84%
And maybe you fall asleep,
or you go deep inside,

00:02:31.420 --> 00:02:33.400 align:middle line:84%
but afterwards,
you feel refreshed.

00:02:33.400 --> 00:02:34.860 align:middle line:90%
And it still works for people.

00:02:34.860 --> 00:02:35.980 align:middle line:90%
It's still wonderful.

00:02:35.980 --> 00:02:38.110 align:middle line:90%
But some people today--

00:02:38.110 --> 00:02:40.420 align:middle line:84%
they do it, or other
forms of meditation,

00:02:40.420 --> 00:02:41.560 align:middle line:90%
and they get bored with it.

00:02:41.560 --> 00:02:43.255 align:middle line:84%
They don't get the
benefits right away.

00:02:43.255 --> 00:02:44.255 align:middle line:90%
It's kind of a struggle.

00:02:44.255 --> 00:02:45.547 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The monkey mind starts.

00:02:45.547 --> 00:02:48.250 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And the mind starts
going around and so forth.

00:02:48.250 --> 00:02:51.400 align:middle line:84%
And particularly women, not so
much men-- but still, many men

00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:53.410 align:middle line:84%
get bored with it or
don't see the point of it.

00:02:53.410 --> 00:02:55.415 align:middle line:84%
But many women are trying,
and they're trying.

00:02:55.415 --> 00:02:57.790 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you go to India,
where a lot of these techniques

00:02:57.790 --> 00:03:00.490 align:middle line:84%
were developed,
mantra meditations--

00:03:00.490 --> 00:03:03.350 align:middle line:84%
repeating a mantra-- if
you ask women in India,

00:03:03.350 --> 00:03:04.725 align:middle line:84%
do you meditate,
they go, oh, no.

00:03:04.725 --> 00:03:06.190 align:middle line:84%
It's too difficult--
too difficult

00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:08.530 align:middle line:84%
because my mind is
jumping around too much.

00:03:08.530 --> 00:03:10.930 align:middle line:84%
And back in the day, when
Buddha was teaching meditation,

00:03:10.930 --> 00:03:12.970 align:middle line:84%
Shankar was teaching
meditation, all these--

00:03:12.970 --> 00:03:13.870 align:middle line:90%
where it came from--

00:03:13.870 --> 00:03:15.820 align:middle line:90%
primarily, it was taught to men.

00:03:15.820 --> 00:03:17.410 align:middle line:84%
And it was taught
to men because it

00:03:17.410 --> 00:03:19.300 align:middle line:90%
helped strengthen masculinity.

00:03:19.300 --> 00:03:23.320 align:middle line:84%
To empty the mind is the
opposite of opening the heart.

00:03:23.320 --> 00:03:25.300 align:middle line:84%
Women were to open
their heart to increase

00:03:25.300 --> 00:03:28.240 align:middle line:84%
the female energies, for
women to find their ground.

00:03:28.240 --> 00:03:30.010 align:middle line:84%
And for men, if they
got too emotional,

00:03:30.010 --> 00:03:32.200 align:middle line:84%
like angry or
aggressive or whatever,

00:03:32.200 --> 00:03:34.820 align:middle line:84%
they would learn to
empty the mind, detach--

00:03:34.820 --> 00:03:36.743 align:middle line:84%
so the whole thing of
learning detachment.

00:03:36.743 --> 00:03:39.160 align:middle line:84%
Now, it turns out-- now that
we have modern science-- when

00:03:39.160 --> 00:03:42.370 align:middle line:84%
you learn to empty your mind,
your testosterone levels

00:03:42.370 --> 00:03:43.840 align:middle line:90%
will start to rise.

00:03:43.840 --> 00:03:45.440 align:middle line:90%
It's good for men.

00:03:45.440 --> 00:03:47.882 align:middle line:84%
But for women, if they're
trying to empty their mind,

00:03:47.882 --> 00:03:49.840 align:middle line:84%
and they need to get over
to their female side,

00:03:49.840 --> 00:03:51.670 align:middle line:90%
it may not be as productive.

00:03:51.670 --> 00:03:53.650 align:middle line:84%
If you look at yoga
classes today-- you know,

00:03:53.650 --> 00:03:55.870 align:middle line:84%
actually, my dad taught me
yoga at three years old.

00:03:55.870 --> 00:03:56.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:03:56.670 --> 00:03:58.990 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: We had seven kids,
and he put the mat out.

00:03:58.990 --> 00:03:59.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my goodness.

00:03:59.990 --> 00:04:02.380 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And Houston, Texas--
who would've thought?

00:04:02.380 --> 00:04:05.140 align:middle line:84%
And we're doing our yoga
postures as little kids.

00:04:05.140 --> 00:04:07.130 align:middle line:84%
And then when I went to
India, I was so proud.

00:04:07.130 --> 00:04:07.930 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to India.

00:04:07.930 --> 00:04:09.340 align:middle line:90%
I'm getting up to do my yoga.

00:04:09.340 --> 00:04:11.090 align:middle line:90%
All the yogis do it alone.

00:04:11.090 --> 00:04:12.280 align:middle line:90%
It's a solitary thing.

00:04:12.280 --> 00:04:15.020 align:middle line:84%
Because whenever you're
alone, you're male hormones

00:04:15.020 --> 00:04:15.820 align:middle line:90%
get produced.

00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:18.320 align:middle line:84%
When you connect with
others, your female hormones

00:04:18.320 --> 00:04:19.120 align:middle line:90%
get produced.

00:04:19.120 --> 00:04:21.640 align:middle line:84%
And for men, particularly,
they need way

00:04:21.640 --> 00:04:23.570 align:middle line:90%
more testosterone than women.

00:04:23.570 --> 00:04:25.450 align:middle line:84%
So meditation was a
way you did alone.

00:04:25.450 --> 00:04:26.800 align:middle line:90%
You did yoga postures.

00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:27.913 align:middle line:90%
You did that alone.

00:04:27.913 --> 00:04:30.246 align:middle line:84%
Today, you see all the women
going to the yoga studios--

00:04:30.246 --> 00:04:30.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes.

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:31.720 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: --but they're
doing it together.

00:04:31.720 --> 00:04:32.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:04:32.050 --> 00:04:33.880 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And they're doing
it to beautiful music.

00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:35.950 align:middle line:84%
And they're doing it with
someone guiding them.

00:04:35.950 --> 00:04:38.920 align:middle line:84%
Guided meditation
stimulates estrogen.

00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:41.350 align:middle line:84%
Whereas doing your own thing,
repeating a mantra over

00:04:41.350 --> 00:04:43.900 align:middle line:84%
and over and over,
calms the mind

00:04:43.900 --> 00:04:45.780 align:middle line:90%
if you need more testosterone.

00:04:45.780 --> 00:04:48.070 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you take
meditation techniques,

00:04:48.070 --> 00:04:50.710 align:middle line:84%
and you look at what's happening
today in the world, women,

00:04:50.710 --> 00:04:52.750 align:middle line:84%
particularly, are way
on their male side

00:04:52.750 --> 00:04:55.460 align:middle line:84%
and often can't get back
to their female side.

00:04:55.460 --> 00:04:57.100 align:middle line:84%
So to do a technique
that helps produce

00:04:57.100 --> 00:04:59.230 align:middle line:84%
testosterone,
emptying the mind, can

00:04:59.230 --> 00:05:01.750 align:middle line:84%
be very boring and difficult
and challenging for them.

00:05:01.750 --> 00:05:03.333 align:middle line:84%
They don't get the
immediate benefits.

00:05:03.333 --> 00:05:04.910 align:middle line:90%
Some women do, but not all.

00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:08.320 align:middle line:84%
So being an expert on gender
differences in this whole thing

00:05:08.320 --> 00:05:11.650 align:middle line:84%
that I do for the last 40
years, and then before that 10

00:05:11.650 --> 00:05:15.960 align:middle line:84%
years just teaching meditation
and being with the Maharishi,

00:05:15.960 --> 00:05:18.580 align:middle line:84%
I was able to recognize a
technique that works as well

00:05:18.580 --> 00:05:20.130 align:middle line:90%
for women as works for men.

00:05:20.130 --> 00:05:21.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Ah, so we
get the oxytocin

00:05:21.810 --> 00:05:24.133 align:middle line:90%
and those great hormones.

00:05:24.133 --> 00:05:26.550 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: You get the female
hormones and the male hormones.

00:05:26.550 --> 00:05:28.008 align:middle line:84%
Because ultimately,
what we want is

00:05:28.008 --> 00:05:31.500 align:middle line:84%
to get into the flow, where
your genius comes forth,

00:05:31.500 --> 00:05:33.542 align:middle line:84%
and it's a effortless
flow of meditation.

00:05:33.542 --> 00:05:35.250 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to
experience that today,

00:05:35.250 --> 00:05:35.970 align:middle line:90%
with this technique.

00:05:35.970 --> 00:05:36.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Which is great.

00:05:36.600 --> 00:05:38.645 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And it was never
taught in the past.

00:05:38.645 --> 00:05:40.020 align:middle line:84%
And the reason it
wasn't taught--

00:05:40.020 --> 00:05:43.170 align:middle line:84%
it was known in
the secret masters.

00:05:43.170 --> 00:05:45.588 align:middle line:84%
And I have studied in
Tibet, with masters,

00:05:45.588 --> 00:05:47.880 align:middle line:84%
and I've learned some of this
from them and adopted it.

00:05:47.880 --> 00:05:50.228 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can I ask you how
did you meet the Maharishi?

00:05:50.228 --> 00:05:51.770 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: How did I
meet the Maharishi?

00:05:51.770 --> 00:05:53.350 align:middle line:90%
Uh, let me go back.

00:05:53.350 --> 00:05:54.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:05:54.150 --> 00:05:55.422 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: OK.

00:05:55.422 --> 00:05:56.880 align:middle line:84%
I went to the
introductory lecture.

00:05:56.880 --> 00:05:58.680 align:middle line:84%
I learned transcendental
meditation.

00:05:58.680 --> 00:06:01.860 align:middle line:84%
And then that year,
Maharishi came to America

00:06:01.860 --> 00:06:03.450 align:middle line:84%
for the first time,
for a big course.

00:06:03.450 --> 00:06:04.783 align:middle line:90%
It was in Poland Springs, Maine.

00:06:04.783 --> 00:06:06.540 align:middle line:84%
There were 1,000
people, 1,000 hippies.

00:06:06.540 --> 00:06:09.060 align:middle line:84%
We all went up there for
a month to hear lectures

00:06:09.060 --> 00:06:10.620 align:middle line:90%
from him all day long.

00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:12.810 align:middle line:84%
And the first lecture,
I was kind of late.

00:06:12.810 --> 00:06:15.720 align:middle line:84%
I got there, and I'm sitting
in the back of 1,000 people,

00:06:15.720 --> 00:06:18.303 align:middle line:84%
and I said, this is not
going to happen again.

00:06:18.303 --> 00:06:19.470 align:middle line:90%
But I was just a little kid.

00:06:19.470 --> 00:06:21.012 align:middle line:84%
I was like the
youngest person there,

00:06:21.012 --> 00:06:24.240 align:middle line:84%
like 17 years old with all
these grown-up 20-year-olds

00:06:24.240 --> 00:06:25.380 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:06:25.380 --> 00:06:28.372 align:middle line:84%
And so I vowed I was never
going to sit in the back again.

00:06:28.372 --> 00:06:30.330 align:middle line:84%
But they wouldn't let me
sit up front because I

00:06:30.330 --> 00:06:31.288 align:middle line:90%
wasn't in the in crowd.

00:06:31.288 --> 00:06:32.872 align:middle line:84%
There was this whole
section of people

00:06:32.872 --> 00:06:35.140 align:middle line:84%
who'd been with him in
India and various things.

00:06:35.140 --> 00:06:36.180 align:middle line:90%
So I pointed myself.

00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:38.280 align:middle line:84%
The next day, I got up
really early went there.

00:06:38.280 --> 00:06:41.277 align:middle line:84%
And I started pretending
like I was the usher--

00:06:41.277 --> 00:06:43.110 align:middle line:84%
and who could go up
front and who could not.

00:06:43.110 --> 00:06:45.693 align:middle line:84%
And I had a usher's seat, and I
would sit in the usher's seat.

00:06:45.693 --> 00:06:47.310 align:middle line:90%
So I'd be right in the front.

00:06:47.310 --> 00:06:49.890 align:middle line:84%
And then so I got to hang
around him a lot that way,

00:06:49.890 --> 00:06:51.780 align:middle line:90%
appointing myself as the usher.

00:06:51.780 --> 00:06:54.280 align:middle line:84%
Then what would happen is
that he went to West Coast

00:06:54.280 --> 00:06:55.080 align:middle line:90%
to do a course.

00:06:55.080 --> 00:06:56.520 align:middle line:84%
And nobody from the
East Coast could

00:06:56.520 --> 00:06:57.720 align:middle line:90%
go because it was sold out--

00:06:57.720 --> 00:06:59.850 align:middle line:84%
1,000 people at
Humboldt University.

00:06:59.850 --> 00:07:01.710 align:middle line:84%
Big hippie thing--
Maharishi was there.

00:07:01.710 --> 00:07:05.340 align:middle line:84%
Great lectures-- all excitement
in the new hippie age.

00:07:05.340 --> 00:07:07.280 align:middle line:90%
And I just didn't listen to him.

00:07:07.280 --> 00:07:08.280 align:middle line:90%
They wouldn't let me in.

00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:09.420 align:middle line:90%
I just went.

00:07:09.420 --> 00:07:10.770 align:middle line:90%
I hitchhiked across the country.

00:07:10.770 --> 00:07:13.300 align:middle line:84%
I hitchhiked over there--
had hardly any money.

00:07:13.300 --> 00:07:14.870 align:middle line:90%
And this was really funny.

00:07:14.870 --> 00:07:15.670 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't get in.

00:07:15.670 --> 00:07:16.570 align:middle line:90%
They wouldn't register me.

00:07:16.570 --> 00:07:16.980 align:middle line:90%
You're not allowed.

00:07:16.980 --> 00:07:18.188 align:middle line:90%
You were at the other course.

00:07:18.188 --> 00:07:19.077 align:middle line:90%
So I was little.

00:07:19.077 --> 00:07:20.910 align:middle line:84%
So the Maharishi would
come in the back door

00:07:20.910 --> 00:07:25.050 align:middle line:84%
with his entourage of rich
and famous and VIP people.

00:07:25.050 --> 00:07:26.460 align:middle line:90%
And he'd come by.

00:07:26.460 --> 00:07:28.383 align:middle line:84%
I'd sneak in and go
right up behind him

00:07:28.383 --> 00:07:29.550 align:middle line:90%
because he was a little guy.

00:07:29.550 --> 00:07:32.008 align:middle line:84%
And I'd stand right behind him
and walk through every time,

00:07:32.008 --> 00:07:34.180 align:middle line:84%
pretending like I
was one of the VIPs.

00:07:34.180 --> 00:07:35.610 align:middle line:84%
I did this every
day for a month.

00:07:35.610 --> 00:07:36.410 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:07:36.410 --> 00:07:39.540 align:middle line:90%
So then he did his--

00:07:39.540 --> 00:07:42.450 align:middle line:84%
he did his only teacher
training program in America.

00:07:42.450 --> 00:07:45.480 align:middle line:84%
It was a three-month
in-residence course here

00:07:45.480 --> 00:07:47.680 align:middle line:90%
at Estes Park, in Colorado.

00:07:47.680 --> 00:07:48.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, wow.

00:07:48.480 --> 00:07:50.160 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: So again,
I applied for that.

00:07:50.160 --> 00:07:52.327 align:middle line:84%
And they wouldn't accept
me because I was too young.

00:07:52.327 --> 00:07:54.810 align:middle line:84%
You had to be in your
20s, and I was 17 or 18.

00:07:54.810 --> 00:07:56.400 align:middle line:90%
And so I went anyway.

00:07:56.400 --> 00:07:57.390 align:middle line:90%
I said but I'm here.

00:07:57.390 --> 00:07:59.390 align:middle line:84%
And they said, well, you
can't become a teacher.

00:07:59.390 --> 00:08:00.280 align:middle line:90%
I said you'll see.

00:08:00.280 --> 00:08:03.660 align:middle line:84%
And so I basically would
share and shine, show up,

00:08:03.660 --> 00:08:05.328 align:middle line:90%
and share my experiences.

00:08:05.328 --> 00:08:06.870 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, they
said I couldn't.

00:08:06.870 --> 00:08:08.787 align:middle line:84%
And I went to him, and
I said I want to do it.

00:08:08.787 --> 00:08:09.720 align:middle line:90%
And he said OK.

00:08:09.720 --> 00:08:11.115 align:middle line:90%
And it was always me pushing.

00:08:11.115 --> 00:08:11.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:08:11.400 --> 00:08:12.270 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: I always pushed.

00:08:12.270 --> 00:08:12.570 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:08:12.570 --> 00:08:13.555 align:middle line:90%
And then he knew me.

00:08:13.555 --> 00:08:14.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You had goals though.

00:08:14.390 --> 00:08:15.223 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: I had goals.

00:08:15.223 --> 00:08:16.160 align:middle line:90%
I had motivation.

00:08:16.160 --> 00:08:18.120 align:middle line:84%
I was just like I'm
going to get in there.

00:08:18.120 --> 00:08:19.290 align:middle line:90%
I just leaned in.

00:08:19.290 --> 00:08:21.150 align:middle line:84%
And I ended up taking
every course he ever

00:08:21.150 --> 00:08:23.790 align:middle line:84%
taught to the public, during
the next three or four years.

00:08:23.790 --> 00:08:26.220 align:middle line:84%
And then he only gave
talks to his people,

00:08:26.220 --> 00:08:28.140 align:middle line:84%
and I started teaching
those courses as well,

00:08:28.140 --> 00:08:29.570 align:middle line:90%
as teacher training programs.

00:08:29.570 --> 00:08:32.070 align:middle line:84%
But during that time, we'd have
these rounding courses where

00:08:32.070 --> 00:08:34.169 align:middle line:90%
you'd meditate six hours a day.

00:08:34.169 --> 00:08:35.109 align:middle line:90%
You'd meditate awhile.

00:08:35.109 --> 00:08:35.909 align:middle line:90%
Do some yoga.

00:08:35.909 --> 00:08:36.472 align:middle line:90%
Then meditate awhile.

00:08:36.472 --> 00:08:36.690 align:middle line:90%
Do some yoga.

00:08:36.690 --> 00:08:37.669 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Guided meditation?

00:08:37.669 --> 00:08:38.909 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: No, you'd
be in your rooms,

00:08:38.909 --> 00:08:40.179 align:middle line:90%
all separately, doing this.

00:08:40.179 --> 00:08:40.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:08:40.580 --> 00:08:41.705 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Called it rounding.

00:08:41.705 --> 00:08:43.140 align:middle line:90%
You'd do breathing exercise.

00:08:43.140 --> 00:08:45.720 align:middle line:84%
First you'd do yoga postures,
then breathing exercise, then

00:08:45.720 --> 00:08:47.160 align:middle line:90%
meditate 30 minutes.

00:08:47.160 --> 00:08:50.417 align:middle line:84%
Then yoga postures,
breathing exercise, and then

00:08:50.417 --> 00:08:51.250 align:middle line:90%
meditate 30 minutes.

00:08:51.250 --> 00:08:51.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Those are the rounds?

00:08:51.720 --> 00:08:54.780 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And you do rounding,
maybe five, six rounds a day.

00:08:54.780 --> 00:08:57.280 align:middle line:84%
Well, after a while, I
started doing way more.

00:08:57.280 --> 00:08:59.790 align:middle line:90%
And I started sharing a lot.

00:08:59.790 --> 00:09:01.530 align:middle line:90%
And I had stellar experiences.

00:09:01.530 --> 00:09:03.930 align:middle line:84%
And then I got to be
his personal assistant.

00:09:03.930 --> 00:09:07.960 align:middle line:84%
His personal assistant got
sick, and his other assistant

00:09:07.960 --> 00:09:08.760 align:middle line:90%
go and got sick.

00:09:08.760 --> 00:09:10.930 align:middle line:84%
And the other one got
kicked out for bad behavior.

00:09:10.930 --> 00:09:12.240 align:middle line:90%
So we had no assistants.

00:09:12.240 --> 00:09:13.905 align:middle line:90%
So there were nine VIP guys.

00:09:13.905 --> 00:09:15.030 align:middle line:90%
These were all rich people.

00:09:15.030 --> 00:09:17.893 align:middle line:84%
Because he had people around him
who could afford it and travel

00:09:17.893 --> 00:09:18.810 align:middle line:90%
with him and all this.

00:09:18.810 --> 00:09:19.610 align:middle line:90%
And I couldn't.

00:09:19.610 --> 00:09:20.827 align:middle line:90%
But so then nine were there.

00:09:20.827 --> 00:09:22.410 align:middle line:84%
And now, they were
all waiting in line

00:09:22.410 --> 00:09:24.610 align:middle line:84%
to be picked as the
new personal assistant.

00:09:24.610 --> 00:09:25.920 align:middle line:90%
So I went and sat in the line.

00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:28.770 align:middle line:84%
And they said no, you can't
be here-- you're not a VIP.

00:09:28.770 --> 00:09:30.100 align:middle line:90%
So I was like really depressed.

00:09:30.100 --> 00:09:30.900 align:middle line:90%
I went to my room.

00:09:30.900 --> 00:09:31.305 align:middle line:90%
I cried.

00:09:31.305 --> 00:09:32.220 align:middle line:90%
[INAUDIBLE]

00:09:32.220 --> 00:09:34.020 align:middle line:84%
The next morning, I just
happened to get up early.

00:09:34.020 --> 00:09:35.980 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, I'll
just get up before them.

00:09:35.980 --> 00:09:37.980 align:middle line:84%
So I went up, and I went
and sat in the chair,

00:09:37.980 --> 00:09:39.930 align:middle line:90%
waiting for them to come up.

00:09:39.930 --> 00:09:41.760 align:middle line:84%
And what Maharishi
would say to people--

00:09:41.760 --> 00:09:42.900 align:middle line:84%
which is when he
was ready, he had

00:09:42.900 --> 00:09:45.275 align:middle line:84%
people go away because everybody
wanted to be around him.

00:09:45.275 --> 00:09:47.560 align:middle line:90%
He'd say, good to go and rest.

00:09:47.560 --> 00:09:48.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, OK.

00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:49.560 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Good to go and rest.

00:09:49.560 --> 00:09:52.050 align:middle line:84%
So I was sitting
there in the morning,

00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:53.448 align:middle line:90%
and the next VIP guy came up.

00:09:53.448 --> 00:09:54.990 align:middle line:84%
And he says, what
are you doing here?

00:09:54.990 --> 00:09:56.660 align:middle line:90%
I said, I'm the new assistant.

00:09:56.660 --> 00:09:58.063 align:middle line:90%
And he said, what do you mean?

00:09:58.063 --> 00:09:59.730 align:middle line:84%
And I said, yeah, I'm
the new assistant,

00:09:59.730 --> 00:10:02.040 align:middle line:90%
and it's good to go and rest.

00:10:02.040 --> 00:10:02.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:10:02.840 --> 00:10:04.530 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And so everybody
who came in, I said it's

00:10:04.530 --> 00:10:05.370 align:middle line:90%
good to go and rest.

00:10:05.370 --> 00:10:06.290 align:middle line:90%
It's good to go and rest.

00:10:06.290 --> 00:10:06.950 align:middle line:90%
I didn't lie.

00:10:06.950 --> 00:10:08.492 align:middle line:84%
I just said it's
good to go and rest.

00:10:08.492 --> 00:10:10.427 align:middle line:84%
I kicked everybody off
the floor for two days.

00:10:10.427 --> 00:10:12.510 align:middle line:84%
So Maharishi was forced
to push his little button,

00:10:12.510 --> 00:10:15.688 align:middle line:84%
and I would come in, and I would
come in to take over the job.

00:10:15.688 --> 00:10:18.355 align:middle line:84%
So I never wanted to ask because
I was afraid of being rejected.

00:10:18.355 --> 00:10:19.893 align:middle line:90%
You're too young.

00:10:19.893 --> 00:10:20.810 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES] So anyway--

00:10:20.810 --> 00:10:21.947 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Just had a will.

00:10:21.947 --> 00:10:23.030 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: I just had a will.

00:10:23.030 --> 00:10:26.260 align:middle line:84%
And then he went on a trip, a
tour of America, at that time.

00:10:26.260 --> 00:10:27.380 align:middle line:90%
I had hardly any money.

00:10:27.380 --> 00:10:28.880 align:middle line:90%
I had $150.

00:10:28.880 --> 00:10:31.040 align:middle line:84%
But at that time, there
was a tour from Europe,

00:10:31.040 --> 00:10:33.445 align:middle line:90%
around America, for $121.

00:10:33.445 --> 00:10:34.820 align:middle line:84%
So I spent almost
all of my money

00:10:34.820 --> 00:10:37.740 align:middle line:84%
on this ticket, Tour America,
for $120, around in a circle.

00:10:37.740 --> 00:10:38.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:10:38.540 --> 00:10:40.160 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: As long as you're in a
circle, going back to Europe,

00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:41.180 align:middle line:90%
things were cheap then.

00:10:41.180 --> 00:10:42.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:10:42.050 --> 00:10:43.550 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And he was
touring America.

00:10:43.550 --> 00:10:45.157 align:middle line:90%
So I bought the ticket.

00:10:45.157 --> 00:10:46.740 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sitting here
as his assistant,

00:10:46.740 --> 00:10:47.900 align:middle line:84%
and people are saying,
oh, Maharishi I'd

00:10:47.900 --> 00:10:48.960 align:middle line:90%
like to come with you.

00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:49.970 align:middle line:90%
He'd say best to stay.

00:10:49.970 --> 00:10:50.940 align:middle line:90%
Best to stay.

00:10:50.940 --> 00:10:52.410 align:middle line:84%
He didn't want to travel
with all these people.

00:10:52.410 --> 00:10:53.510 align:middle line:90%
It was a headache.

00:10:53.510 --> 00:10:56.060 align:middle line:84%
So anyway, so nobody was
there to travel with them.

00:10:56.060 --> 00:10:58.070 align:middle line:84%
And if I had asked, he
would have said best

00:10:58.070 --> 00:11:00.230 align:middle line:84%
to stay because he had
people on the other end that

00:11:00.230 --> 00:11:00.644 align:middle line:90%
would take care of him.

00:11:00.644 --> 00:11:01.225 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You knew not to ask.

00:11:01.225 --> 00:11:01.500 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:02.700 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: So I didn't ask.

00:11:02.700 --> 00:11:03.853 align:middle line:90%
I just bought the ticket.

00:11:03.853 --> 00:11:05.395 align:middle line:84%
[CHUCKLES] So we
got on the airplane.

00:11:05.395 --> 00:11:06.936 align:middle line:84%
I'm sitting next to
him on the plane.

00:11:06.936 --> 00:11:07.940 align:middle line:90%
He just laughed at me.

00:11:07.940 --> 00:11:09.780 align:middle line:84%
He just said this
kid has got this far.

00:11:09.780 --> 00:11:10.020 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:11:10.020 --> 00:11:11.385 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: He recognized you.

00:11:11.385 --> 00:11:13.590 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: He probably
saw himself in me

00:11:13.590 --> 00:11:15.855 align:middle line:84%
because he was his guru's
personal assistant and so,

00:11:15.855 --> 00:11:16.655 align:middle line:90%
for him.

00:11:16.655 --> 00:11:18.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, wonderful.

00:11:18.080 --> 00:11:21.587 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Anyway, so I went to
that and persisted with him.

00:11:21.587 --> 00:11:22.670 align:middle line:90%
We were so sweet together.

00:11:22.670 --> 00:11:24.385 align:middle line:90%
He was like a father to me.

00:11:24.385 --> 00:11:26.510 align:middle line:84%
And also when he would
teach his meditation courses

00:11:26.510 --> 00:11:28.315 align:middle line:84%
on these rounding
courses, I just

00:11:28.315 --> 00:11:29.690 align:middle line:84%
happened to be
really good at it.

00:11:29.690 --> 00:11:31.200 align:middle line:90%
And I'm very dedicated to it.

00:11:31.200 --> 00:11:33.650 align:middle line:84%
So there's lots of
stories about that.

00:11:33.650 --> 00:11:34.640 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:11:34.640 --> 00:11:36.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The stories,
I'm sure, could go on--

00:11:36.100 --> 00:11:37.320 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Just go on and
on and on about it.

00:11:37.320 --> 00:11:38.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --forever.

00:11:38.120 --> 00:11:40.580 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: But I learned,
really, through meditation,

00:11:40.580 --> 00:11:44.000 align:middle line:84%
how to have altered
higher consciousness.

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:48.810 align:middle line:84%
And I probably would've still
been there, but at nine years,

00:11:48.810 --> 00:11:51.470 align:middle line:84%
I had brought-- my
brother was bipolar.

00:11:51.470 --> 00:11:53.585 align:middle line:84%
And a meditation-- I
brought him to Switzerland,

00:11:53.585 --> 00:11:54.710 align:middle line:90%
where we were at that time.

00:11:54.710 --> 00:11:56.065 align:middle line:90%
And it just didn't help him.

00:11:56.065 --> 00:11:57.860 align:middle line:84%
And he said, I just
gotta go back, John.

00:11:57.860 --> 00:11:59.030 align:middle line:90%
I said, OK, OK.

00:11:59.030 --> 00:12:00.710 align:middle line:84%
But I just felt my
brother's suffering.

00:12:00.710 --> 00:12:03.570 align:middle line:84%
And here I am, in the glory
of my life, and you know--

00:12:03.570 --> 00:12:04.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You had already
written your books and--

00:12:04.880 --> 00:12:05.680 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: No, no.

00:12:05.680 --> 00:12:07.560 align:middle line:84%
No books-- this is
all just meditation.

00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:09.278 align:middle line:90%
I'm on the posters with him.

00:12:09.278 --> 00:12:11.570 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they had my brain--
they had this flying thing,

00:12:11.570 --> 00:12:14.420 align:middle line:84%
where you're hopping around, and
they have my picture doing it.

00:12:14.420 --> 00:12:16.970 align:middle line:84%
And my brain chemical,
my brainwaves

00:12:16.970 --> 00:12:19.300 align:middle line:90%
as a display in 3,600 cities.

00:12:19.300 --> 00:12:21.560 align:middle line:84%
You know, Maharishi's
picture, then here I am.

00:12:21.560 --> 00:12:25.440 align:middle line:84%
So I was a well-known person in
the TM movement at that time.

00:12:25.440 --> 00:12:26.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:12:26.990 --> 00:12:28.640 align:middle line:90%
Wow, very fortunate.

00:12:28.640 --> 00:12:30.190 align:middle line:90%
Or, as you could say, destiny.

00:12:30.190 --> 00:12:30.980 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: It definitely destiny.

00:12:30.980 --> 00:12:31.480 align:middle line:90%
This was destiny.

00:12:31.480 --> 00:12:32.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Definitely.

00:12:32.280 --> 00:12:35.320 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And actually, my
last conversation with him, I

00:12:35.320 --> 00:12:37.030 align:middle line:84%
was asking about what
my future would be.

00:12:37.030 --> 00:12:39.800 align:middle line:84%
And he says in 10
years, you will own

00:12:39.800 --> 00:12:41.480 align:middle line:90%
this movement is what he said.

00:12:41.480 --> 00:12:43.230 align:middle line:84%
But that was my last
conversation with him

00:12:43.230 --> 00:12:45.930 align:middle line:90%
because my brother was sick.

00:12:45.930 --> 00:12:48.390 align:middle line:84%
And I couldn't be in
this glorious place

00:12:48.390 --> 00:12:50.940 align:middle line:84%
when my brother's sick and
meditation didn't help.

00:12:50.940 --> 00:12:55.090 align:middle line:84%
So I felt in my heart I just had
to go find an answer for him.

00:12:55.090 --> 00:12:55.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm.

00:12:55.890 --> 00:12:58.265 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And I flew out to
California to study psychology,

00:12:58.265 --> 00:13:00.200 align:middle line:84%
thinking that could
help my brother.

00:13:00.200 --> 00:13:02.990 align:middle line:84%
And trying to help my brother
launched my whole career

00:13:02.990 --> 00:13:06.080 align:middle line:84%
because studying
psychology, I then started

00:13:06.080 --> 00:13:08.898 align:middle line:84%
having a counseling practice
and realized that there's

00:13:08.898 --> 00:13:10.190 align:middle line:90%
a better way to counsel people.

00:13:10.190 --> 00:13:12.470 align:middle line:84%
And that was by understanding
where people come

00:13:12.470 --> 00:13:13.900 align:middle line:90%
from without right or wrong.

00:13:13.900 --> 00:13:14.756 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The differences
without judgement.

00:13:14.756 --> 00:13:16.464 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Yeah, the
differences came forth.

00:13:16.464 --> 00:13:19.640 align:middle line:84%
And meditation gave me
the ability to be curious,

00:13:19.640 --> 00:13:21.550 align:middle line:84%
rather than to
immediately judge,

00:13:21.550 --> 00:13:24.170 align:middle line:84%
and to study, rather
than to give advice.

00:13:24.170 --> 00:13:25.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: To observe.

00:13:25.100 --> 00:13:26.600 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: To observe
and feel empathy.

00:13:26.600 --> 00:13:28.610 align:middle line:90%
And it prepared me for that.

00:13:28.610 --> 00:13:31.490 align:middle line:84%
And then I could be this great
counselor and great husband

00:13:31.490 --> 00:13:33.020 align:middle line:90%
and father of my children.

00:13:33.020 --> 00:13:34.790 align:middle line:84%
Meditation is a
foundation where you

00:13:34.790 --> 00:13:36.902 align:middle line:90%
can find unconditional love.

00:13:36.902 --> 00:13:38.360 align:middle line:84%
If you're not full
within yourself,

00:13:38.360 --> 00:13:39.950 align:middle line:84%
you're always looking
to be filled up.

00:13:39.950 --> 00:13:41.533 align:middle line:84%
And if you're looking
to be filled up,

00:13:41.533 --> 00:13:43.562 align:middle line:84%
you look to control
when you're empty.

00:13:43.562 --> 00:13:45.020 align:middle line:84%
And so you give up
control, and you

00:13:45.020 --> 00:13:47.540 align:middle line:84%
have this openness when you're
already fulfilled inside.

00:13:47.540 --> 00:13:49.520 align:middle line:84%
And that's what meditation
can give people.

00:13:49.520 --> 00:13:51.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It also has
probably helped you

00:13:51.380 --> 00:13:53.780 align:middle line:84%
with the amount of
grief that you have

00:13:53.780 --> 00:13:55.820 align:middle line:90%
experienced in your lifetime.

00:13:55.820 --> 00:13:59.510 align:middle line:84%
You've had several very close
people to you pass away.

00:13:59.510 --> 00:14:00.680 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Oh, devastating.

00:14:00.680 --> 00:14:03.380 align:middle line:84%
You know, I have this charmed
life, but at the same time,

00:14:03.380 --> 00:14:06.590 align:middle line:90%
I have these big devastations.

00:14:06.590 --> 00:14:08.540 align:middle line:84%
I could go on, but
just very shortly,

00:14:08.540 --> 00:14:11.930 align:middle line:84%
my little brother, Jimmy, who
I actually came to America

00:14:11.930 --> 00:14:13.737 align:middle line:90%
to help--

00:14:13.737 --> 00:14:16.070 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't help him, and he
ended up committing suicide.

00:14:16.070 --> 00:14:16.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:14:16.870 --> 00:14:19.530 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: So that was a
really hard thing on me.

00:14:19.530 --> 00:14:21.920 align:middle line:90%
And then there was my father.

00:14:21.920 --> 00:14:24.710 align:middle line:84%
On my honeymoon with
Bonnie, my wife,

00:14:24.710 --> 00:14:28.050 align:middle line:84%
got a call that he'd been found
dead in the trunk of his car.

00:14:28.050 --> 00:14:33.580 align:middle line:84%
He had picked up a hitchhiker
and ended up dead in his car

00:14:33.580 --> 00:14:34.580 align:middle line:90%
by the side of the road.

00:14:34.580 --> 00:14:35.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm.

00:14:35.610 --> 00:14:38.120 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And here's the
irony of the magic of life.

00:14:38.120 --> 00:14:40.730 align:middle line:84%
My last conversation-- I had
brought Bonnie to meet my dad,

00:14:40.730 --> 00:14:44.920 align:middle line:84%
and he gives her a tour
of Houston, where I lived.

00:14:44.920 --> 00:14:45.980 align:middle line:90%
And I said to my dad--

00:14:45.980 --> 00:14:47.600 align:middle line:84%
I said, now, dad, I
want to give you advice.

00:14:47.600 --> 00:14:49.433 align:middle line:84%
Now I'm grown up, and
I can give you advice.

00:14:49.433 --> 00:14:50.930 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh,
what's that John?

00:14:50.930 --> 00:14:53.870 align:middle line:84%
I said, it's not safe
to pick up hitchhikers.

00:14:53.870 --> 00:14:55.790 align:middle line:90%
He was a very generous man.

00:14:55.790 --> 00:14:59.000 align:middle line:84%
The tour we were on was of
the poor section of Houston,

00:14:59.000 --> 00:15:01.865 align:middle line:84%
where he had started the
clubs teaching them sports.

00:15:01.865 --> 00:15:03.990 align:middle line:84%
He bought all the sports
equipment and the baseball

00:15:03.990 --> 00:15:05.323 align:middle line:90%
equipment, and started all that.

00:15:05.323 --> 00:15:07.365 align:middle line:84%
So this is what he was so
proud of because he was

00:15:07.365 --> 00:15:08.880 align:middle line:90%
helping all these poor people.

00:15:08.880 --> 00:15:10.520 align:middle line:84%
And then, suddenly,
I say, but, dad,

00:15:10.520 --> 00:15:12.320 align:middle line:90%
you can't pick up hitchhikers.

00:15:12.320 --> 00:15:15.950 align:middle line:84%
And he said, John, some
men, when they retire,

00:15:15.950 --> 00:15:17.510 align:middle line:90%
they go on safari.

00:15:17.510 --> 00:15:19.150 align:middle line:90%
For me, I pick up hitchhikers.

00:15:19.150 --> 00:15:19.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ooh.

00:15:19.950 --> 00:15:20.940 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: He would help people.

00:15:20.940 --> 00:15:21.740 align:middle line:90%
Give them money.

00:15:21.740 --> 00:15:23.227 align:middle line:90%
Drive them places.

00:15:23.227 --> 00:15:25.560 align:middle line:84%
And then a week later, I'm
on the honeymoon with Bonnie.

00:15:25.560 --> 00:15:27.070 align:middle line:84%
And I hear the call,
and he's found.

00:15:27.070 --> 00:15:30.340 align:middle line:84%
And that was a big
turning point for me.

00:15:30.340 --> 00:15:32.490 align:middle line:84%
And when I look at my
tragedies, they always

00:15:32.490 --> 00:15:33.720 align:middle line:90%
have a gift in them.

00:15:33.720 --> 00:15:34.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:15:34.080 --> 00:15:34.860 align:middle line:90%
You found a gift in that.

00:15:34.860 --> 00:15:35.730 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Found the gift in that.

00:15:35.730 --> 00:15:37.980 align:middle line:84%
I found the gift in Jimmy
because that helped open me up

00:15:37.980 --> 00:15:39.110 align:middle line:84%
to the whole thing
of psychology.

00:15:39.110 --> 00:15:39.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:15:39.910 --> 00:15:42.060 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And my whole destiny
came through that act

00:15:42.060 --> 00:15:43.590 align:middle line:90%
of wanting to help him.

00:15:43.590 --> 00:15:46.800 align:middle line:90%
My dad-- I got into the trunk.

00:15:46.800 --> 00:15:48.600 align:middle line:84%
My family's all standing
around, but I just

00:15:48.600 --> 00:15:50.670 align:middle line:84%
felt like I had to relive
what he went through.

00:15:50.670 --> 00:15:53.077 align:middle line:84%
It was terrifying, the thought
of being left in a trunk.

00:15:53.077 --> 00:15:54.160 align:middle line:90%
Because he wasn't damaged.

00:15:54.160 --> 00:15:55.260 align:middle line:90%
He was just put in the trunk.

00:15:55.260 --> 00:15:56.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You just wanted
to know, didn't you?

00:15:56.550 --> 00:15:57.592 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: I wanted to know.

00:15:57.592 --> 00:15:59.160 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to connect with my dad.

00:15:59.160 --> 00:16:01.320 align:middle line:84%
And I saw where he had
taken a screwdriver

00:16:01.320 --> 00:16:03.390 align:middle line:84%
and banged for help,
asking for help.

00:16:03.390 --> 00:16:05.910 align:middle line:84%
And three times, people
called the police,

00:16:05.910 --> 00:16:07.110 align:middle line:90%
and the police didn't come.

00:16:07.110 --> 00:16:08.790 align:middle line:84%
Again, that's the
lack of communication.

00:16:08.790 --> 00:16:10.743 align:middle line:84%
Until my mother called,
the fourth call,

00:16:10.743 --> 00:16:12.660 align:middle line:84%
and they said, yeah,
that car's been reported.

00:16:12.660 --> 00:16:13.960 align:middle line:90%
We'll go check it out.

00:16:13.960 --> 00:16:15.210 align:middle line:90%
Because he wasn't killed.

00:16:15.210 --> 00:16:18.520 align:middle line:84%
He died in the trunk
from heat asphyxiation.

00:16:18.520 --> 00:16:20.850 align:middle line:84%
But he was crying
out, making noises.

00:16:20.850 --> 00:16:24.120 align:middle line:84%
And the next thing he did is
he unscrewed the back light.

00:16:24.120 --> 00:16:25.560 align:middle line:90%
And so you pull it in.

00:16:25.560 --> 00:16:26.640 align:middle line:90%
Now, this is a Mercedes.

00:16:26.640 --> 00:16:29.320 align:middle line:84%
Back then, they didn't have
a release to open the trunk.

00:16:29.320 --> 00:16:30.550 align:middle line:90%
So he was trapped.

00:16:30.550 --> 00:16:34.110 align:middle line:84%
And so when I'm in the
trunk, I pull this back,

00:16:34.110 --> 00:16:36.900 align:middle line:84%
and just without thinking,
I put my hand out.

00:16:36.900 --> 00:16:39.150 align:middle line:84%
And as I'm pulling my
hand back, my brother

00:16:39.150 --> 00:16:41.190 align:middle line:84%
on the outside of
the trunk says,

00:16:41.190 --> 00:16:43.960 align:middle line:84%
John, see if you can reach
around to the button.

00:16:43.960 --> 00:16:47.190 align:middle line:84%
And I reached around, pushed the
button, and opened the trunk.

00:16:47.190 --> 00:16:48.130 align:middle line:90%
And that's a tragedy.

00:16:48.130 --> 00:16:48.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That easy.

00:16:48.930 --> 00:16:51.905 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: That's the tragedy of it
is that the solution was there,

00:16:51.905 --> 00:16:53.280 align:middle line:84%
but he just didn't
think about it

00:16:53.280 --> 00:16:56.640 align:middle line:84%
because when you're in the box,
you're only trying to get out.

00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:59.250 align:middle line:84%
You're not thinking from
the other point of view.

00:16:59.250 --> 00:17:00.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That is
such a huge lesson.

00:17:00.900 --> 00:17:01.950 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: It was a
huge lesson for me.

00:17:01.950 --> 00:17:03.330 align:middle line:84%
And that's the birth
of "Men Are from Mars,

00:17:03.330 --> 00:17:05.817 align:middle line:84%
Women Are from Venus" is that
whenever there's a problem,

00:17:05.817 --> 00:17:07.859 align:middle line:84%
look at it from the other
person's point of view.

00:17:07.859 --> 00:17:08.579 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really.

00:17:08.579 --> 00:17:10.537 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: We should always
know that when there's

00:17:10.537 --> 00:17:12.974 align:middle line:84%
a miscommunication, we're
looking at our point of view

00:17:12.974 --> 00:17:15.599 align:middle line:84%
as opposed to trying to look at
it from the other point of view

00:17:15.599 --> 00:17:17.349 align:middle line:90%
and blend them together.

00:17:17.349 --> 00:17:19.950 align:middle line:84%
And that was an inspiration
for me in my life.

00:17:19.950 --> 00:17:21.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, we
can thank your dad.

00:17:21.450 --> 00:17:22.500 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yeah, thank my dad.

00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:24.000 align:middle line:84%
And he's always with
me because of that.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:24.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:24.800 --> 00:17:26.940 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Then, my sister--

00:17:26.940 --> 00:17:29.760 align:middle line:84%
younger sister-- died
of early Alzheimer's.

00:17:29.760 --> 00:17:30.560 align:middle line:90%
So that was awful.

00:17:30.560 --> 00:17:31.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my goodness.

00:17:31.280 --> 00:17:32.790 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Awful what they--
they drug them up, and they

00:17:32.790 --> 00:17:34.665 align:middle line:84%
put them in these
hospitals to collect money.

00:17:34.665 --> 00:17:37.260 align:middle line:90%
And it just-- it was horrible.

00:17:37.260 --> 00:17:39.540 align:middle line:90%
Then there's my mother.

00:17:39.540 --> 00:17:42.310 align:middle line:90%
She died of an accident.

00:17:42.310 --> 00:17:45.040 align:middle line:84%
She had asked them to come and
repair the heater at her house

00:17:45.040 --> 00:17:46.890 align:middle line:84%
because it was
putting off gassing.

00:17:46.890 --> 00:17:49.790 align:middle line:84%
And they didn't come, and
then she died from poison.

00:17:49.790 --> 00:17:50.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Carbon monoxide.

00:17:50.790 --> 00:17:52.207 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Carbon
monoxide poisoning.

00:17:52.207 --> 00:17:54.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So these are not
old-age-related deaths.

00:17:54.790 --> 00:17:56.130 align:middle line:90%
These are tragedies.

00:17:56.130 --> 00:17:56.645 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: These are traumas.

00:17:56.645 --> 00:17:57.540 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, these are tragedies.

00:17:57.540 --> 00:17:58.582 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Each one of them.

00:17:58.582 --> 00:18:03.210 align:middle line:84%
And it is amazing that you
are able to sit and really

00:18:03.210 --> 00:18:04.790 align:middle line:90%
teach about love.

00:18:04.790 --> 00:18:05.590 align:middle line:90%
It's incredible.

00:18:05.590 --> 00:18:08.130 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Yeah, well, I think
here's a thought for everyone

00:18:08.130 --> 00:18:12.210 align:middle line:84%
is that we all come into this
world with destinies, but we--

00:18:12.210 --> 00:18:14.700 align:middle line:84%
it's like trying to fly
from LA to New York.

00:18:14.700 --> 00:18:16.510 align:middle line:84%
A plane is actually
never on track.

00:18:16.510 --> 00:18:17.845 align:middle line:90%
It's always deviating.

00:18:17.845 --> 00:18:18.720 align:middle line:90%
It's self-correcting.

00:18:18.720 --> 00:18:21.180 align:middle line:84%
The wind blows it this way--
the computer self corrects.

00:18:21.180 --> 00:18:23.220 align:middle line:84%
It's never really
going straight.

00:18:23.220 --> 00:18:27.108 align:middle line:84%
So our life, to be in
tune, tune into our flow,

00:18:27.108 --> 00:18:28.650 align:middle line:84%
we're always going
to be off balance.

00:18:28.650 --> 00:18:31.805 align:middle line:84%
And it's only by being off
balance and coming back

00:18:31.805 --> 00:18:33.680 align:middle line:84%
into balance that we
can find the flow again.

00:18:33.680 --> 00:18:34.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Isn't that the truth.

00:18:34.020 --> 00:18:36.103 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Because no one's
ever going to be perfect.

00:18:36.103 --> 00:18:38.310 align:middle line:84%
So mistakes and
tragedies and losses--

00:18:38.310 --> 00:18:41.220 align:middle line:84%
they all help us to
come back to more,

00:18:41.220 --> 00:18:42.510 align:middle line:90%
even when we make mistakes.

00:18:42.510 --> 00:18:44.260 align:middle line:84%
Because when my brother
committed suicide,

00:18:44.260 --> 00:18:45.900 align:middle line:84%
I felt so much
guilt for not being

00:18:45.900 --> 00:18:48.120 align:middle line:84%
able to help him and be a better
brother when I was growing up.

00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:50.670 align:middle line:84%
Not like I was a bad brother,
but you just look at everything

00:18:50.670 --> 00:18:51.750 align:middle line:84%
you wish you could
have done differently.

00:18:51.750 --> 00:18:52.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:18:52.110 --> 00:18:53.485 align:middle line:84%
It's important to
talk about that

00:18:53.485 --> 00:18:57.175 align:middle line:84%
because not everybody finds the
reason in the death of a loved

00:18:57.175 --> 00:18:58.470 align:middle line:90%
one, like you have.

00:18:58.470 --> 00:19:02.940 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Yeah, and so what I
looked at is I felt my guilt,

00:19:02.940 --> 00:19:05.887 align:middle line:84%
and I used that to
become a better person.

00:19:05.887 --> 00:19:07.470 align:middle line:84%
See, that's what
guilt can do for you.

00:19:07.470 --> 00:19:09.120 align:middle line:84%
When you feel the guilt,
you let it go because you're

00:19:09.120 --> 00:19:10.440 align:middle line:90%
going to learn from it.

00:19:10.440 --> 00:19:12.690 align:middle line:84%
Everybody makes
mistakes, but you

00:19:12.690 --> 00:19:14.880 align:middle line:84%
grow if you take on
your guilt, and you let

00:19:14.880 --> 00:19:16.740 align:middle line:90%
it go with self forgiveness.

00:19:16.740 --> 00:19:18.570 align:middle line:90%
And that helps us to adjust.

00:19:18.570 --> 00:19:20.650 align:middle line:84%
Our heart opens and says
I want to be better.

00:19:20.650 --> 00:19:21.770 align:middle line:90%
I want to be better.

00:19:21.770 --> 00:19:24.390 align:middle line:84%
And with Jimmy,
that was my pledge.

00:19:24.390 --> 00:19:26.550 align:middle line:84%
I look back on his
childhood, and I saw

00:19:26.550 --> 00:19:29.480 align:middle line:90%
how he always looked up to me.

00:19:29.480 --> 00:19:31.240 align:middle line:90%
And I was this little guy.

00:19:31.240 --> 00:19:33.090 align:middle line:90%
But who looked up to him?

00:19:33.090 --> 00:19:34.830 align:middle line:84%
So I was always sort
of thinking about me

00:19:34.830 --> 00:19:36.810 align:middle line:84%
and wasn't always
pumping him up.

00:19:36.810 --> 00:19:38.370 align:middle line:84%
So I said to myself
when he died,

00:19:38.370 --> 00:19:40.770 align:middle line:84%
one of the places looking,
is I pledge to myself,

00:19:40.770 --> 00:19:42.865 align:middle line:84%
when somebody is there
for me, I'm always

00:19:42.865 --> 00:19:43.990 align:middle line:90%
going to be there for them.

00:19:43.990 --> 00:19:45.930 align:middle line:90%
I won't forget them.

00:19:45.930 --> 00:19:47.430 align:middle line:90%
And that was a big thing for me.

00:19:47.430 --> 00:19:47.910 align:middle line:90%
Then--

00:19:47.910 --> 00:19:49.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: A beautiful way to
live your life, by the way.

00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:50.460 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:50.880 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yeah, yeah.

00:19:50.880 --> 00:19:51.960 align:middle line:90%
Be grateful.

00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:54.810 align:middle line:84%
And so when I wrote
my first book--

00:19:54.810 --> 00:19:58.720 align:middle line:84%
before "Men Are from Mars" was
"Men, Women and Relationships."

00:19:58.720 --> 00:20:01.230 align:middle line:90%
And no publisher wanted me.

00:20:01.230 --> 00:20:02.610 align:middle line:84%
And a friend of
mine had a friend

00:20:02.610 --> 00:20:05.467 align:middle line:90%
with a small distribution house.

00:20:05.467 --> 00:20:07.050 align:middle line:84%
And they took that
book, and they sold

00:20:07.050 --> 00:20:09.993 align:middle line:90%
50,000 copies, which is huge.

00:20:09.993 --> 00:20:11.410 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, how
did they do it?

00:20:11.410 --> 00:20:14.130 align:middle line:84%
So suddenly, an agent found
me and sent-- because no agent

00:20:14.130 --> 00:20:15.150 align:middle line:90%
wanted me at the time.

00:20:15.150 --> 00:20:16.930 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't any famous
person or whatever.

00:20:16.930 --> 00:20:19.925 align:middle line:84%
And they said, I can sell
your book to New York.

00:20:19.925 --> 00:20:21.300 align:middle line:84%
And Bonnie and I
were so excited.

00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:21.690 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my god.

00:20:21.690 --> 00:20:23.040 align:middle line:84%
This book, "Men, Women
and Relationships"--

00:20:23.040 --> 00:20:23.880 align:middle line:90%
New York's going to buy.

00:20:23.880 --> 00:20:25.540 align:middle line:84%
In those days, New
York was everything.

00:20:25.540 --> 00:20:26.915 align:middle line:84%
If you have a New
York publisher,

00:20:26.915 --> 00:20:28.980 align:middle line:90%
you just didn't get in stores.

00:20:28.980 --> 00:20:31.890 align:middle line:84%
So we're so excited, and I
called up the publishers.

00:20:31.890 --> 00:20:33.570 align:middle line:84%
Group West is what
they were called.

00:20:33.570 --> 00:20:34.650 align:middle line:90%
I said, good news--

00:20:34.650 --> 00:20:36.060 align:middle line:90%
New York's going to buy my book.

00:20:36.060 --> 00:20:39.295 align:middle line:84%
And they said, yes, good
news for you, but not for us.

00:20:39.295 --> 00:20:40.095 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yes.

00:20:40.095 --> 00:20:42.762 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Because they said, every
time we have a successful book,

00:20:42.762 --> 00:20:43.620 align:middle line:90%
they take it away.

00:20:43.620 --> 00:20:44.740 align:middle line:90%
We don't get to build it.

00:20:44.740 --> 00:20:46.440 align:middle line:84%
And he says, will you at
least let us talk to you

00:20:46.440 --> 00:20:47.815 align:middle line:84%
and show you that
we think we can

00:20:47.815 --> 00:20:49.840 align:middle line:90%
do a great job with your book.

00:20:49.840 --> 00:20:51.030 align:middle line:90%
I said yes.

00:20:51.030 --> 00:20:52.410 align:middle line:90%
And I had to at least do that.

00:20:52.410 --> 00:20:52.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:20:52.770 --> 00:20:54.780 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Everybody I talked
to said, this is your dream.

00:20:54.780 --> 00:20:55.540 align:middle line:90%
Go with New York.

00:20:55.540 --> 00:20:56.085 align:middle line:90%
This is your dream.

00:20:56.085 --> 00:20:57.480 align:middle line:84%
My agent-- they're
ready to buy your book.

00:20:57.480 --> 00:21:00.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then you had these
people that started with you.

00:21:00.270 --> 00:21:01.562 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: So I go to the meeting.

00:21:01.562 --> 00:21:03.312 align:middle line:84%
And there I am in the
meeting, and they're

00:21:03.312 --> 00:21:04.632 align:middle line:90%
telling me what they can do.

00:21:04.632 --> 00:21:06.090 align:middle line:84%
And I know it's
not as much as what

00:21:06.090 --> 00:21:07.720 align:middle line:90%
New York could do for my book.

00:21:07.720 --> 00:21:09.720 align:middle line:84%
But then the president
of the company was there.

00:21:09.720 --> 00:21:12.130 align:middle line:84%
He says, so will you
trust us and let us do it?

00:21:12.130 --> 00:21:14.640 align:middle line:84%
And when he did it, it was
the voice of my brother Jimmy.

00:21:14.640 --> 00:21:17.520 align:middle line:84%
I felt the spirit of
Jimmy right there.

00:21:17.520 --> 00:21:19.770 align:middle line:84%
And these were the
people who had helped me

00:21:19.770 --> 00:21:20.860 align:middle line:90%
when nobody else would.

00:21:20.860 --> 00:21:21.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:21:21.880 --> 00:21:23.790 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And so I was not
about to take this book away

00:21:23.790 --> 00:21:24.270 align:middle line:90%
from them.

00:21:24.270 --> 00:21:25.853 align:middle line:84%
So he said, will you
give us the book?

00:21:25.853 --> 00:21:27.270 align:middle line:90%
And I said yes.

00:21:27.270 --> 00:21:28.340 align:middle line:90%
And my wife was shocked.

00:21:28.340 --> 00:21:30.180 align:middle line:90%
My agent was shocked.

00:21:30.180 --> 00:21:31.785 align:middle line:84%
Because my heart
was open-- pure.

00:21:31.785 --> 00:21:33.410 align:middle line:84%
That was the spirit
talking through me.

00:21:33.410 --> 00:21:35.130 align:middle line:90%
This is my lesson.

00:21:35.130 --> 00:21:36.953 align:middle line:90%
And Jimmy was there.

00:21:36.953 --> 00:21:38.745 align:middle line:84%
So I remember then
getting in the elevator,

00:21:38.745 --> 00:21:41.340 align:middle line:84%
and my agent said to me,
what are you going to do?

00:21:41.340 --> 00:21:42.460 align:middle line:90%
What are you going to do?

00:21:42.460 --> 00:21:44.210 align:middle line:90%
You know we can sell that book.

00:21:44.210 --> 00:21:47.070 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'll
write another one.

00:21:47.070 --> 00:21:48.210 align:middle line:90%
You can write another one?

00:21:48.210 --> 00:21:50.250 align:middle line:90%
I said, I can write it better.

00:21:50.250 --> 00:21:52.700 align:middle line:84%
And in three months,
I had finished it.

00:21:52.700 --> 00:21:53.820 align:middle line:90%
Every day, I worked--

00:21:53.820 --> 00:21:55.370 align:middle line:90%
I took my kids to school.

00:21:55.370 --> 00:21:56.520 align:middle line:90%
I babysitted Lauren.

00:21:56.520 --> 00:21:58.612 align:middle line:90%
I wrote for six hours.

00:21:58.612 --> 00:21:59.820 align:middle line:90%
Every week, wrote a chapter--

00:21:59.820 --> 00:22:00.630 align:middle line:90%
12 chapters.

00:22:00.630 --> 00:22:01.260 align:middle line:90%
It was done.

00:22:01.260 --> 00:22:02.790 align:middle line:84%
It was the easiest
book I've ever

00:22:02.790 --> 00:22:05.220 align:middle line:84%
written because it came
right from that place

00:22:05.220 --> 00:22:08.400 align:middle line:84%
in my heart, which is
do the right thing,

00:22:08.400 --> 00:22:09.720 align:middle line:90%
and the universe supports you.

00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:10.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that
was "Mars, Venus."

00:22:10.830 --> 00:22:13.170 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And that's "Men Are from
Mars, Women Are from Venus."

00:22:13.170 --> 00:22:14.253 align:middle line:90%
So what a beautiful thing.

00:22:14.253 --> 00:22:16.460 align:middle line:84%
Again, that's growing
from learning a lesson

00:22:16.460 --> 00:22:18.210 align:middle line:84%
from something and
letting your heart grow

00:22:18.210 --> 00:22:20.490 align:middle line:84%
through these mishaps to
help us become better.

00:22:20.490 --> 00:22:22.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you were
operating your life

00:22:22.170 --> 00:22:24.000 align:middle line:90%
not from a place of survival.

00:22:24.000 --> 00:22:27.600 align:middle line:84%
And these years of
meditation and learning

00:22:27.600 --> 00:22:30.900 align:middle line:84%
how to work with the
universe and the higher good

00:22:30.900 --> 00:22:33.595 align:middle line:84%
for yourself, I think
would have contributed

00:22:33.595 --> 00:22:34.845 align:middle line:90%
to making decisions like that.

00:22:34.845 --> 00:22:36.762 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Oh, well,
everything-- you see, we all

00:22:36.762 --> 00:22:38.760 align:middle line:84%
have the prefrontal
cortex, the monkey brain,

00:22:38.760 --> 00:22:39.900 align:middle line:90%
and the instinctive brain.

00:22:39.900 --> 00:22:42.570 align:middle line:84%
All of our emotional, negative
emotions, fears, doubts,

00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:44.880 align:middle line:84%
angers, frustrations,
hesitate-- that's all monkey

00:22:44.880 --> 00:22:46.290 align:middle line:90%
brain talking.

00:22:46.290 --> 00:22:48.570 align:middle line:84%
And when you learn
through meditation

00:22:48.570 --> 00:22:51.180 align:middle line:84%
to strengthen the
prefrontal cortex,

00:22:51.180 --> 00:22:54.180 align:middle line:84%
then you connect to the big
boss, which is your spirit.

00:22:54.180 --> 00:22:55.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:22:55.020 --> 00:22:57.960 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And spirit-- even
now, as my wife has passed--

00:22:57.960 --> 00:22:59.710 align:middle line:90%
and she died of cancer.

00:22:59.710 --> 00:23:00.825 align:middle line:90%
And it was tragic.

00:23:00.825 --> 00:23:03.450 align:middle line:84%
It's just so beautiful, and then
suddenly, within a few months,

00:23:03.450 --> 00:23:03.950 align:middle line:90%
it was gone.

00:23:03.950 --> 00:23:05.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes

00:23:05.010 --> 00:23:06.510 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And she's
still in my heart.

00:23:06.510 --> 00:23:09.390 align:middle line:84%
But such a tragedy, and
I'm grieving even now.

00:23:09.390 --> 00:23:12.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm going through months and
months of the grieving process.

00:23:12.220 --> 00:23:12.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Rightfully so.

00:23:12.590 --> 00:23:14.460 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: There's still always
this little star up there

00:23:14.460 --> 00:23:16.560 align:middle line:84%
in my higher self that says
you're going to get through it.

00:23:16.560 --> 00:23:17.728 align:middle line:90%
Everything's going to be OK.

00:23:17.728 --> 00:23:19.020 align:middle line:90%
You're going to grow from this.

00:23:19.020 --> 00:23:21.120 align:middle line:84%
You're going to be a
better man from this.

00:23:21.120 --> 00:23:23.070 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I already
am a better person

00:23:23.070 --> 00:23:26.145 align:middle line:84%
from growing because your
mind goes back, and it says,

00:23:26.145 --> 00:23:27.270 align:middle line:90%
oh, I wish I had done this.

00:23:27.270 --> 00:23:28.020 align:middle line:90%
I wish I had done that.

00:23:28.020 --> 00:23:29.475 align:middle line:84%
That's what guilt
can do-- reflection.

00:23:29.475 --> 00:23:30.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Those are the lessons.

00:23:30.570 --> 00:23:31.350 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: As long
as you can let it

00:23:31.350 --> 00:23:33.990 align:middle line:84%
go is realizing you have to
come from the unconditional love

00:23:33.990 --> 00:23:37.482 align:middle line:84%
for yourself and others,
which meditation can give you.

00:23:37.482 --> 00:23:38.940 align:middle line:84%
Because through
meditation, you can

00:23:38.940 --> 00:23:40.830 align:middle line:90%
connect with the life stream.

00:23:40.830 --> 00:23:42.377 align:middle line:90%
You connect with the spirit.

00:23:42.377 --> 00:23:44.460 align:middle line:84%
And in the spirit world,
there's no good, no bads.

00:23:44.460 --> 00:23:46.360 align:middle line:90%
It's all unconditional.

00:23:46.360 --> 00:23:49.440 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So through these
techniques and this experience,

00:23:49.440 --> 00:23:51.810 align:middle line:84%
for nine years of meditation
and really working

00:23:51.810 --> 00:23:55.380 align:middle line:84%
with these tools, you can take
your experience with Bonnie

00:23:55.380 --> 00:23:58.560 align:middle line:84%
and say, OK, I did that, and
maybe I feel badly about that,

00:23:58.560 --> 00:24:00.730 align:middle line:90%
but I'll do better next time.

00:24:00.730 --> 00:24:02.640 align:middle line:84%
And you don't give
yourself judgment or shame

00:24:02.640 --> 00:24:03.808 align:middle line:90%
or get stuck in that place.

00:24:03.808 --> 00:24:05.100 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: It's not getting stuck.

00:24:05.100 --> 00:24:05.900 align:middle line:90%
I feel it.

00:24:05.900 --> 00:24:06.740 align:middle line:90%
I feel guilty.

00:24:06.740 --> 00:24:07.740 align:middle line:90%
I should have done this.

00:24:07.740 --> 00:24:10.110 align:middle line:84%
I should have-- basically,
I should have saved her.

00:24:10.110 --> 00:24:11.470 align:middle line:90%
That's the emotional side of it.

00:24:11.470 --> 00:24:12.270 align:middle line:90%
I failed her.

00:24:12.270 --> 00:24:13.070 align:middle line:90%
I saved her.

00:24:13.070 --> 00:24:16.530 align:middle line:84%
And of course, in the end, she
said, John, you're my hero.

00:24:16.530 --> 00:24:18.350 align:middle line:90%
You did everything.

00:24:18.350 --> 00:24:19.150 align:middle line:90%
It was so sweet.

00:24:19.150 --> 00:24:20.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You did.

00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:20.800 align:middle line:90%
You did.

00:24:20.800 --> 00:24:23.700 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: But what you have to do
is feelings have to come forth.

00:24:23.700 --> 00:24:25.030 align:middle line:90%
The feelings come forth.

00:24:25.030 --> 00:24:29.280 align:middle line:84%
And if you have meditation, you
observe them, and they flow.

00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:32.010 align:middle line:84%
And as feelings, or dirty
feelings or negative feelings--

00:24:32.010 --> 00:24:33.510 align:middle line:90%
they just flow and become pure.

00:24:33.510 --> 00:24:35.640 align:middle line:84%
They clean themselves
if you can feel it,

00:24:35.640 --> 00:24:37.080 align:middle line:90%
and you learn to let go.

00:24:37.080 --> 00:24:39.630 align:middle line:84%
Meditation helps you
to let go and let

00:24:39.630 --> 00:24:41.590 align:middle line:90%
yourself get into the flow.

00:24:41.590 --> 00:24:43.830 align:middle line:84%
So what I saw in
my own experience

00:24:43.830 --> 00:24:45.290 align:middle line:90%
of being a meditator--

00:24:45.290 --> 00:24:47.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Could I ask you really
quick about the grief process?

00:24:47.170 --> 00:24:47.880 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yes.

00:24:47.880 --> 00:24:49.825 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because you really
are an expert in grieving.

00:24:49.825 --> 00:24:51.080 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Yeah, I've written
several books on it.

00:24:51.080 --> 00:24:51.240 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:24:51.240 --> 00:24:52.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You have.

00:24:52.290 --> 00:24:54.720 align:middle line:84%
And through the
grieving process,

00:24:54.720 --> 00:24:57.090 align:middle line:84%
you are letting
the feelings come,

00:24:57.090 --> 00:24:59.490 align:middle line:84%
and then allowing them
to go like a river.

00:24:59.490 --> 00:25:00.600 align:middle line:90%
You're still working.

00:25:00.600 --> 00:25:02.580 align:middle line:84%
You're still doing your
mission, your passion.

00:25:02.580 --> 00:25:03.380 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yes.

00:25:03.380 --> 00:25:05.963 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you are experiencing
the grieving process as well.

00:25:05.963 --> 00:25:08.300 align:middle line:84%
You did a couple of months
where you did nothing.

00:25:08.300 --> 00:25:09.175 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Right, right.

00:25:09.175 --> 00:25:09.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A good six months.

00:25:09.590 --> 00:25:10.815 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: I just wandered
around the house, wailing.

00:25:10.815 --> 00:25:11.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:25:11.040 --> 00:25:12.323 align:middle line:90%
Mm-hmm.

00:25:12.323 --> 00:25:14.740 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: But see, for me, each
time, it comes back to love.

00:25:14.740 --> 00:25:18.030 align:middle line:84%
It's the recognition that I only
miss her because I love her.

00:25:18.030 --> 00:25:19.890 align:middle line:84%
I only feel guilty
because I love her.

00:25:19.890 --> 00:25:22.170 align:middle line:84%
And what heals the heart
is coming back to feeling

00:25:22.170 --> 00:25:23.220 align:middle line:90%
I love her.

00:25:23.220 --> 00:25:24.510 align:middle line:84%
Because there's the feeling
of I don't have you.

00:25:24.510 --> 00:25:25.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of course.

00:25:25.110 --> 00:25:26.250 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: There's
the pain of that.

00:25:26.250 --> 00:25:26.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I want you.

00:25:26.740 --> 00:25:27.870 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: And then I miss you.

00:25:27.870 --> 00:25:28.440 align:middle line:90%
I want you.

00:25:28.440 --> 00:25:29.310 align:middle line:90%
I need you.

00:25:29.310 --> 00:25:31.680 align:middle line:84%
And for me, every little
thing that she did for me,

00:25:31.680 --> 00:25:33.180 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing for myself now.

00:25:33.180 --> 00:25:34.492 align:middle line:90%
So it will bring up grief.

00:25:34.492 --> 00:25:36.450 align:middle line:84%
And then it will bring
up the love of gratitude

00:25:36.450 --> 00:25:37.825 align:middle line:90%
that she did that for me.

00:25:37.825 --> 00:25:39.450 align:middle line:84%
Just the other day,
the most recent one

00:25:39.450 --> 00:25:43.560 align:middle line:84%
was I was rushing home from the
airport, and I asked myself,

00:25:43.560 --> 00:25:44.520 align:middle line:90%
why am I rushing?

00:25:44.520 --> 00:25:47.225 align:middle line:84%
And I'm rushing to
get home to see her.

00:25:47.225 --> 00:25:48.850 align:middle line:84%
It was just like--
and she's not there.

00:25:48.850 --> 00:25:50.460 align:middle line:84%
So again, it brings
up the feelings.

00:25:50.460 --> 00:25:50.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:25:50.760 --> 00:25:52.470 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: And I'll be
doing my laundry,

00:25:52.470 --> 00:25:53.910 align:middle line:90%
and she used to do my laundry.

00:25:53.910 --> 00:25:56.220 align:middle line:84%
So I'm doing the laundry, and
in the beginning, it was like,

00:25:56.220 --> 00:25:57.120 align:middle line:90%
she did this for me.

00:25:57.120 --> 00:25:58.320 align:middle line:90%
I didn't even thank her for it.

00:25:58.320 --> 00:25:58.650 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:25:58.650 --> 00:26:00.630 align:middle line:84%
It would be such
sweetness when you see all

00:26:00.630 --> 00:26:02.270 align:middle line:90%
the things your partner does.

00:26:02.270 --> 00:26:04.305 align:middle line:84%
And now, part of
the healing process

00:26:04.305 --> 00:26:06.960 align:middle line:84%
is when I'm doing my
laundry, she's inside of me.

00:26:06.960 --> 00:26:08.690 align:middle line:84%
I'm folding my T-shirts
the way she did,

00:26:08.690 --> 00:26:10.410 align:middle line:84%
and so I'm feeling
the comfort of her

00:26:10.410 --> 00:26:12.000 align:middle line:90%
still, remembering the love.

00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:14.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But what a great
lesson to those of us who do

00:26:14.340 --> 00:26:15.880 align:middle line:84%
take our relationships
for granted.

00:26:15.880 --> 00:26:16.680 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yeah.

00:26:16.680 --> 00:26:16.980 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:26:16.980 --> 00:26:19.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And to really be
grateful for that moment.

00:26:19.150 --> 00:26:19.950 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:26:19.950 --> 00:26:21.460 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Yeah, and
to me, I just--

00:26:21.460 --> 00:26:24.067 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: For all of the moments.

00:26:24.067 --> 00:26:26.400 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: I miss so much that
first thing in the morning--

00:26:26.400 --> 00:26:27.390 align:middle line:90%
she was a morning person.

00:26:27.390 --> 00:26:28.080 align:middle line:90%
I'm not.

00:26:28.080 --> 00:26:28.350 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:26:28.350 --> 00:26:29.065 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Me neither.

00:26:29.065 --> 00:26:29.600 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: I need to
meditate awhile.

00:26:29.600 --> 00:26:30.400 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:26:30.400 --> 00:26:32.380 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:26:32.380 --> 00:26:34.740 align:middle line:84%
But every morning, I'd
get up, and she would

00:26:34.740 --> 00:26:37.000 align:middle line:90%
be in her little nightgown.

00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:39.645 align:middle line:84%
And she'd greet me a big
smile and her blue eyes.

00:26:39.645 --> 00:26:41.490 align:middle line:84%
And I just said
good morning, honey.

00:26:41.490 --> 00:26:43.500 align:middle line:84%
It's like she had no
problem in the world.

00:26:43.500 --> 00:26:45.417 align:middle line:84%
She could come from that
pure feminine energy.

00:26:45.417 --> 00:26:47.333 align:middle line:84%
Problems would come later
with her, [CHUCKLES]

00:26:47.333 --> 00:26:48.560 align:middle line:90%
but she would start fresh.

00:26:48.560 --> 00:26:49.910 align:middle line:90%
And what a gift that was to me.

00:26:49.910 --> 00:26:50.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Every day.

00:26:50.310 --> 00:26:52.070 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Because all
any man ever wants

00:26:52.070 --> 00:26:53.763 align:middle line:90%
is to see his partner happy.

00:26:53.763 --> 00:26:55.680 align:middle line:84%
And every woman wants
her husband to be happy.

00:26:55.680 --> 00:26:56.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:26:56.480 --> 00:26:59.235 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: So just to know
that that hug was such a--

00:26:59.235 --> 00:27:00.327 align:middle line:90%
would just anchor.

00:27:00.327 --> 00:27:02.910 align:middle line:84%
And so every day, I wake up and
I imagine giving her that hug.

00:27:02.910 --> 00:27:04.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you feel
these feelings of grief,

00:27:04.560 --> 00:27:06.685 align:middle line:84%
and you go through this,
but yet, at the same time,

00:27:06.685 --> 00:27:10.680 align:middle line:84%
you have this base, this
strong base that you've learned

00:27:10.680 --> 00:27:12.230 align:middle line:90%
through decades of meditation.

00:27:12.230 --> 00:27:13.030 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Yeah.

00:27:13.030 --> 00:27:16.470 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it gives you the anchor
to come back to what is true.

00:27:16.470 --> 00:27:19.085 align:middle line:84%
See, part of the pain
of losing someone

00:27:19.085 --> 00:27:21.950 align:middle line:84%
is I'll never love again because
no one will ever replace her,

00:27:21.950 --> 00:27:23.900 align:middle line:90%
so I'll never love again.

00:27:23.900 --> 00:27:24.960 align:middle line:90%
But that's not true.

00:27:24.960 --> 00:27:26.320 align:middle line:90%
I will love again.

00:27:26.320 --> 00:27:28.630 align:middle line:84%
So the inner-self
knows what is true.

